race.comment: GOOLOO BUCKY (9) is starting to build a nice record, enhanced last start when he just got the prize in a Class 3 over this distance at Nowra. Probably won't find this a lot harder and with that extra run under the belt he is capable of winning again. FACEOFF (8) came with a well-timed run to win a BM58 over today's journey at Moruya last time out. Nicely drawn and although this is a tougher test he drops 4kgs to compensate. EQUILIBRIST (2) ran his best race of the campaign last start when a closing third over 1300m at this track. Down a little in class this time and is cherry ripe after four runs back from a spell. TAI LUNG (6) won at Warwick Farm two back then battled away okay in heavy ground at Rosehill three weeks ago. Beautifully graded today and Grima's claim brings him in very well. KING OF DRAGONS (5) finished less than three lengths behind a smart one in Gatsby's at Randwick a fortnight ago. Big chance on that form.
